''See also: [[Haw]]''
==English==

===Interjection===
'''haw'''

# An imitation of laughter, often used to express scorn or disbelief.  Often duplicated or triplicated (''haw haw'' or ''haw haw haw'').
#: ''You think that song was good?  Haw!''
# An instruction for a horse or other animal to turn left.

====Related terms====
*[[hem and haw]] (1)
*[[hum and haw]] (1)
*[[gee haw whimmy diddle]] (2)

====See also====
*[[ha]] (1)
*[[gee]] (2)

====Usage notes====
''Haw'' as an imitation of laughter is generally more used outside the US.  US usage prefers ''ha''.  The instruction to an animal is always ''haw''.

===Verb===
'''haw'''

# (''of an animal'') To turn left or cause to turn left.
#: ''This horse won't haw when I tell him to.''
#: ''You may have to go to the front of the pack and physically haw the lead dog.''

